</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-24_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-25_ pf-text-1">According to the Department for Education, 75% of early years settings in the UK report that well-managed transitions positively impact children’s development.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-27_ pf-text-1">Studies indicate that children who experience smooth transitions are more likely to exhibit better social skills and academic performance.

